A worker came to fix the kitchen floor, and I pretended to be working from home, but in reality, I was editing "Cannot Stop."
If this damned file could just open. (OneDrive is really crap.)
*hacker's voice* I'm in.
He started drilling, and the noise was super loud. Great.
I turned the air purifier to maximum, it felt a bit too aggressive, but I did smell the wood shavings, so it's justified, especially since he opposed wearing a mask. And I do need to protect myself, right?
I really want to go back to sleep, but I can't sleep until he leaves.
The good news is, Chapter 4 is finally edited!
Chapter 5 is really long and super anxiety-inducing. Yeah! It's so exciting.
Currently searching and replacing...➡️ellipses, there are 54 in this chapter😅
But I still insist on this point. Most natural languages are incoherent, especially when people are emotionally excited.
The floor repairman is vacuuming, hoping that this means he is almost done.
He went out (it sounded like) cutting something. I took a quick look at the progress. There's still a lot of work to do :(
There are still 7 pages left in Chapter 5. This is still my favorite chapter, and the manuscript is in quite good shape, mainly requiring layout adjustments, and some minor changes to active voice and conciseness. But I really need to take a break and have a cup of tea, while that guy is still messing around in my kitchen.
He started using the vacuum cleaner again. I hope this is a good omen.
The floor repairman for the kitchen is gone!
He told me that he quoted the price for repairing the entire floor, but the landlord was too stingy and only agreed to pay for the repair of the part near the door that had already rotted. It feels much better.
I was having tea in the garden, and the air purifier was working hard in the kitchen, purifying the air in the room!
